This version addresses the following issues:

1. Users may not join on Monday (e.g., joining on Wednesday, leaving only 5 days in the week).

2. The last few days of a month may not constitute a full week.

3. If only "complete 7 days" are displayed, user data will be missing, especially for new users or users crossing month lines.

The current monthly statistics use the approach of "Calculated Target = Monthly Target × (Days Elapsed / Total Days in Month)".

The same logic is reused weekly: Weekly Battery Consumption = Actual Cumulative + Progress = Days Elapsed / 7

Current work:

First: Adding the basic framework for weekly statistics (Date Range + Days Elapsed + Weekly Cumulative Battery Consumption)

Second: Adding progress percentage, note prompts, and sorting daily_records.
